Steps:
1. Select Category "General";
2. Click Rename Category button;
3. Enter new name as "Foundations";
4. Click Save button.

1. Select Category "IT";
2. Click Create New Course button;
3. Enter Course Name as "Web Development";
4. Click Save button.

1. Select Course "Web Development";
2. Click Edit Course button;
3. Change name to "Frontend Development";
4. Click Save button.

1. Navigate to Archived Courses tab;
2. Click Restore button for course "Frontend Development";
3. Confirm restoration.

1. Open Course "Web Development";
2. Click Add Session button;
3. Enter Session Name as "Session 1: HTML Basics";
4. Click Save button.

1. Click Edit icon on session;
2. Update Session Name to "Session 1: HTML & CSS Fundamentals";
3. Click Save button.

1. Open Course "Web Development";
2. Click Add Exam button;
3. Enter Exam Name as "Midterm Exam";
4. Click Save button.

1. Click Edit icon on exam;
2. Update Exam Name to "Midterm Practical Exam";
3. Click Save button.

1. Open Attach Material dialog for Session/Exam;
2. Enter Label as "Lecture Slides";
3. Enter URL as "https://drive.google.com/file/d/123/view";
4. Click Save button.

1. Add multiple material rows;
2. Enter valid Labels and Google Drive URLs;
3. Click Save button.

1. Fill Row 1 with valid label and URL;
2. Leave Row 2 completely empty;
3. Click Save button.

1. Enter Label as "Lecture Slides";
2. Leave URL field empty;
3. Click Save button.

1. Leave Label field empty;
2. Enter valid Google Drive URL;
3. Click Save button.

1. Enter Label as "External Site";
2. Enter non-Google Drive URL "https://example.com/file.pdf";
3. Click Save button.
